adjectives.description: unsulky (comparative more unsulky, superlative most unsulky)

examples: I am the one who wakes up nearest to myself, and the continual horror that comes from the realisation of this individuality has made me almost to believe that the reactions of others to my horrible self  […]  are small enough, in comparison, to be counted as the others' loss or to be beaten down by one unsulky thought.
